Sentencas: Thin films of La0.85Sr0.15MnO3 (LSM) are deposited on (1 0 0) silicon wafer and YSZ (yttria-stabilized zircornia) electrolyte substrates by magnetron sputtering using a single-phase LSM target.
Titulo: Growth and characterization of La0.85Sr0.15MnO3 thin films for fuel cell applications

Sentencas: The conditions for sputtering are systematically studied, including substrate temperature (from room temperature to 600 degrees C), the argon background pressure (from 1.2 x 10(-2) to 3.0 x 10(-2) mbar), and deposition time.
Titulo: Growth and characterization of La0.85Sr0.15MnO3 thin films for fuel cell applications

Sentencas: Results show that the optimal conditions for producing a dense, uniform, and crack-free LSM film include a substrate temperature of 600 degrees C and an argon pressure of 1.9 x 10(-2)
Titulo: Growth and characterization of La0.85Sr0.15MnO3 thin films for fuel cell applications
Growth and characterization of La0.85Sr0.15MnO3 thin films for fuel cell applications

Sentencas: Further, a testing cell with a dense LSM film, an YSZ electrolyte membrane, and a porous LSM counter electrode is prepared and the electrochemical properties of the dense LSM film on YSZ substrate are studied.
Titulo: Growth and characterization of La0.85Sr0.15MnO3 thin films for fuel cell applications

Sentencas: It was found that the thickness, morphology, and microstructure of LSM films critically influence the electrochemical properties.
Titulo: Growth and characterization of La0.85Sr0.15MnO3 thin films for fuel cell applications
